\begin_inset Formula $\begin{matrix}f: & \Omega & \longrightarrow & R\\
 & \left(x_{1},\dots x_{n}\right) &  & f\left(x_{1},\dots,x_{n}\right)
\end{matrix}$
\end_inset

.
 Entonces se define 
\begin_inset Formula $df$
\end_inset

 como 
\begin_inset Formula $df:={\displaystyle \sum_{i=1}^{n}\frac{\partial f}{\partial x_{i}}dx_{i}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

, vemos que claramente:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
d\phi\left(\vec{R}\right)=\frac{\partial\phi}{\partial x'}dx'+\frac{\partial\phi}{\partial y'}dy'+\frac{\partial\phi}{\partial z'}dz'=\vec{\nabla}'\phi\left(\vec{R}\right)\cdot\vec{\delta}\label{eq:dphi = gradprima}
